   "source": [
    "# Solving PDEs\n",
    "This notebook is about solving partial differential equations (PDEs) using [finite differences](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finite_difference), but there are a few other [methods out there](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partial_differential_equation#Numerical_solutions) which have their pros and cons. The finite difference method is relatively easy so is a good method to start with.\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose we have the following PDE\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial u}{\\partial t} = \\frac{\\partial^2u}{\\partial t^2}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.integrate import solve_ivp"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# define right hand size of ODEs\n",
    "def rhs(t,u):\n",
    "    RHS = np.zeros(len(u))\n",
    "    h = 1/len(u) # spatial grid size\n",
    "    for i in range(1,len(u)-1):\n",
    "        RHS[i] = (1/h**2)*(u[i-1] - 2*u[i] + u[i+1])\n",
    "\n",
    "    PhiG = -.1*u[0] # flux into the bottom layer\n",
    "    # lower boundary\n",
    "    RHS[0] = (1/h**2)*(-2*u[0] + u[1]) + PhiG\n",
    "\n",
    "    PhiT = 1 # flux into the top layer\n",
    "    # upper boundary\n",
    "    RHS[-1] = (1/h**2)*(u[-2] + -2*u[-1]) + PhiT\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return RHS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The solver successfully reached the end of the integration interval.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "num_of_layers = 20\n",
    "u0 = np.zeros(num_of_layers) # initial condition\n",
    "tspan = [0,10]\n",
    "\n",
    "sol = solve_ivp(rhs,tspan,u0)\n",
    "print(sol.message)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 648x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot\n",
    "z = np.linspace(0,1,len(u0))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 15})\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=[9,5])\n",
    "\n",
    "times = np.logspace(-2,np.log10(tspan[1]),4)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(sol.y[:,0],z,label='t = 0')\n",
    "for time in times:\n",
    "    ind = np.argmin(np.abs(time-sol.t))\n",
    "    ax.plot(sol.y[:,ind],z,label='t ='+'%.3f'%sol.t[ind])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('dimensionless space')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('u')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from numba import njit\n",
    "rhs_jit = njit(rhs)\n",
    "rhs_jit(0,u0) # compiles the function\n",
    "print('',end='')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "1.45 s ± 15.7 ms per loop (mean ± std. dev. of 7 runs, 1 loop each)\n",
      "756 ms ± 7.66 ms per loop (mean ± std. dev. of 7 runs, 1 loop each)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "t1 = %timeit -o solve_ivp(rhs,tspan,u0)\n",
    "t2 = %timeit -o solve_ivp(rhs_jit,tspan,u0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   ]
